WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.747 --> 00:00:02.747
Narrator: Earth.

2
00:00:02.749 --> 00:00:03.879
Fire.

3
00:00:03.883 --> 00:00:06.183
Air.

4
00:00:06.185 --> 00:00:08.115
Water.

5
00:00:08.121 --> 00:00:12.261
Only the Avatar
can master all four elements

6
00:00:12.258 --> 00:00:14.458
and bring balance to the world.

7
00:00:14.460 --> 00:00:17.960
[dramatic music]

8
00:00:20.433 --> 00:00:22.673
- Announcer: Six months ago.
Avatar Korra defeated

9
00:00:22.669 --> 00:00:24.339
Amon and the Equalists.

10
00:00:24.337 --> 00:00:26.307
Since then.
the Council was disbanded

11
00:00:26.306 --> 00:00:29.066
and the United Republic
elected its first president.

12
00:00:29.075 --> 00:00:31.105
Tenzin's brother.
Commander Bumi.

13
00:00:31.110 --> 00:00:33.650
retired and moved
to Air Temple Island

14
00:00:33.646 --> 00:00:35.506
and Korra and her boyfriend. Mako.

15
00:00:35.515 --> 00:00:36.945
have been the talk of the town.

16
00:00:36.950 --> 00:00:38.720
Peace has come to Republic City.

17
00:00:38.718 --> 00:00:40.548
but unbeknownst to the Avatar.

18
00:00:40.553 --> 00:00:43.123
danger now threatens
the Southern Water Tribe.

19
00:00:43.122 --> 00:00:44.522
[horn blares]

20
00:00:44.524 --> 00:00:46.534
- This your first watch?

21
00:00:46.526 --> 00:00:47.686
- Mm-hmm.

22
00:00:47.694 --> 00:00:49.534
- Well then. you'd better keep

23
00:00:49.529 --> 00:00:51.099
your eyes peeled. laddie.

24
00:00:51.097 --> 00:00:54.827
You never know what creatures
lurk in the murky depths.

25
00:00:54.834 --> 00:00:56.804
-[gasps]
[thunder rumbling]

26
00:00:56.803 --> 00:01:01.803
- [chuckling]

27
00:01:04.010 --> 00:01:05.710
- Uh. sir.

28
00:01:05.712 --> 00:01:07.282
- What?

29
00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:08.550
Aah!

30
00:01:08.548 --> 00:01:13.548
- Man overboard!
Man overboard!

31
00:01:19.826 --> 00:01:21.086
[bell dings]

32
00:01:21.094 --> 00:01:24.334
- It's Pro bending night
in Republic City.

33
00:01:24.330 --> 00:01:26.870
and have we got a doozy for you.

34
00:01:26.866 --> 00:01:28.566
Fan favorites.
the Fire Ferrets.

35
00:01:28.568 --> 00:01:30.538
are about to take on
hot newcomers.

36
00:01:30.536 --> 00:01:32.296
the Rhino-Lions.

37
00:01:32.305 --> 00:01:34.805
- Now we all know that
our last match was garbage.

38
00:01:34.807 --> 00:01:35.937
Terrible.

39
00:01:35.942 --> 00:01:37.482
Even Pabu could have done
a better job.

40
00:01:37.477 --> 00:01:38.507
[Pabu chitters]

41
00:01:38.511 --> 00:01:39.951
But that's in the past.

42
00:01:39.946 --> 00:01:42.246
because when you back
a Fire Ferret in the corner.

43
00:01:42.248 --> 00:01:44.218
well. mister.
he comes out fighting!

44
00:01:44.217 --> 00:01:45.247
[Pabu hisses]

45
00:01:45.251 --> 00:01:47.251
So let's get out there

46
00:01:47.253 --> 00:01:49.093
and bend like there's no tomorrow.

47
00:01:49.088 --> 00:01:51.458
Are you with me?

48
00:01:51.457 --> 00:01:55.257
- [sniffs]

49
00:01:55.261 --> 00:01:57.531
[bell dings]

50
00:01:57.530 --> 00:01:59.060
[all grunt]
[buzzer]

51
00:01:59.065 --> 00:02:01.565
- Ooh. the Fire Ferrets
go down in the water

52
00:02:01.567 --> 00:02:03.137
and right into the record books

53
00:02:03.136 --> 00:02:06.036
for the fastest knockout
in pro-bending history.

54
00:02:06.039 --> 00:02:08.809
- Where's Mako when I need him?

55
00:02:08.808 --> 00:02:13.808
[sirens wail.
motorcycle revs]

56
00:02:13.913 --> 00:02:17.083
[tires squeal]

57
00:02:17.083 --> 00:02:22.083
[sirens wail]

58
00:02:27.560 --> 00:02:32.560
[motorcycle revs]

59
00:02:32.799 --> 00:02:37.799
[gasps]

60
00:02:40.306 --> 00:02:45.306
[truck honks]

61
00:02:47.213 --> 00:02:48.513
[tires screech]

62
00:02:48.514 --> 00:02:50.724
[explosion]

63
00:02:50.716 --> 00:02:55.716
[tires screeching]

64
00:02:57.723 --> 00:03:00.133
[men groan]

65
00:03:00.126 --> 00:03:02.956
Looks like you had some car trouble.

66
00:03:02.962 --> 00:03:07.962
Good thing the police are here.

67
00:03:16.943 --> 00:03:19.443
- I think these planes
are finally ready to ship.

68
00:03:19.445 --> 00:03:22.105
- I hate to mention
the elephant-rhino in the room.

69
00:03:22.115 --> 00:03:24.215
but since your father
was thrown in prison.

70
00:03:24.217 --> 00:03:26.077
no company will work with us.

71
00:03:26.085 --> 00:03:27.785
We're nearly bankrupt.

72
00:03:27.787 --> 00:03:29.047
- Don't worry.

73
00:03:29.055 --> 00:03:30.115
I'm going to the South Pole

74
00:03:30.123 --> 00:03:31.493
to meet with someone
who can help us

75
00:03:31.491 --> 00:03:36.491
put Future Industries back on top.

76
00:03:38.531 --> 00:03:43.531
[Oogi grumbles]

77
00:03:49.175 --> 00:03:54.175
- Wah!

78
00:04:06.826 --> 00:04:08.826
- [coughs]

79
00:04:08.828 --> 00:04:12.828
The Avatar is the winner!

80
00:04:12.832 --> 00:04:14.472
- No fair.

81
00:04:14.467 --> 00:04:16.937
You can't go into
the Avatar State to win.

82
00:04:16.936 --> 00:04:18.666
- [raspberries]
- You did what?

83
00:04:18.671 --> 00:04:23.641
The Avatar State is not
to be used as a booster rocket.

84
00:04:23.643 --> 00:04:25.683
You are toying
with a dangerous power

85
00:04:25.678 --> 00:04:27.378
that you obviously do not appreciate.

86
00:04:27.380 --> 00:04:30.520
- It's the "Avatar State."
and I'm the Avatar.

87
00:04:30.516 --> 00:04:32.316
Who appreciates it more than me?

88
00:04:32.318 --> 00:04:34.488
- Clearly. you need
more training to grasp

89
00:04:34.487 --> 00:04:37.117
the depths of
your spiritual connections.

90
00:04:37.123 --> 00:04:39.263
not to mention that
you're still a long way

91
00:04:39.258 --> 00:04:40.828
from mastering airbending.

92
00:04:40.826 --> 00:04:43.026
- I have mastered airbending.

93
00:04:43.029 --> 00:04:45.499
Punch.punch.punch!

94
00:04:45.498 --> 00:04:47.698
See? Mastered.

95
00:04:47.700 --> 00:04:49.670
- Looks pretty good to me.
- [sighs]

96
00:04:49.669 --> 00:04:51.899
Is it too late for you to un-retire

97
00:04:51.904 --> 00:04:53.444
from the United Forces?

98
00:04:53.439 --> 00:04:55.969
- The paperwork's gone through.
little brother.

99
00:04:55.975 --> 00:05:00.975
From now on.
it's 24/7 Bumi time!

100
00:05:01.981 --> 00:05:04.681
- You've mastered
Korra-style airbending.

101
00:05:04.684 --> 00:05:07.854
Now you need
to master real airbending.

102
00:05:07.853 --> 00:05:10.463
Hopefully. our visit
to all of the Air Temples

103
00:05:10.456 --> 00:05:12.316
will give you the inspiration you need

104
00:05:12.325 --> 00:05:15.255
to delve more deeply into your studies.

105
00:05:15.261 --> 00:05:16.731
- Can we see where
Grandpa Aang was born?

106
00:05:16.729 --> 00:05:18.459
- How many lemurs can I have?

107
00:05:18.464 --> 00:05:20.404
- I want to get tattoos.
but instead of arrows

108
00:05:20.399 --> 00:05:21.729
I want lightning bolts.

109
00:05:21.734 --> 00:05:23.274
- You can't get lightning bolts.

110
00:05:23.269 --> 00:05:24.799
That doesn't make any sense.

111
00:05:24.804 --> 00:05:26.644
- You don't make any sense!

112
00:05:26.639 --> 00:05:28.009
- Fight. fight. fight!

113
00:05:28.007 --> 00:05:30.037
[both grumbling]
- No one's fighting.

114
00:05:30.042 --> 00:05:32.612
We're going to have
a wonderful time.

115
00:05:32.612 --> 00:05:34.012
[groans]

116
00:05:34.013 --> 00:05:36.353
Now that the President is in office

117
00:05:36.349 --> 00:05:37.979
and I'm not needed on the Council.

118
00:05:37.984 --> 00:05:40.094
I can finally relax with my family

119
00:05:40.086 --> 00:05:42.446
and give Korra
the attention she needs.

120
00:05:42.455 --> 00:05:44.455
- Great.
More attention.

121
00:05:44.457 --> 00:05:46.557
- [laughs]
Relax?

122
00:05:46.559 --> 00:05:48.459
I'd pay money to see that.

123
00:05:48.461 --> 00:05:52.601
Maybe I'll tag along
just to see "Vacation Tenzin."

124
00:05:52.598 --> 00:05:54.568
- You're not invited.

125
00:05:54.567 --> 00:05:56.697
- Before we go on
your dad's study trip.

126
00:05:56.702 --> 00:05:59.102
we're going to have
some real fun in my hometown

127
00:05:59.105 --> 00:06:00.635
at the Glacier Spirits Festival.

128
00:06:00.640 --> 00:06:02.040
They've got rides. games.

129
00:06:02.041 --> 00:06:04.041
and all kinds
of fried food on sticks.

130
00:06:04.043 --> 00:06:06.043
All: Yay!

131
00:06:06.045 --> 00:06:07.075
[excitedly chattering]

132
00:06:07.079 --> 00:06:09.909
- Yep. there's Vacation Tenzin.

133
00:06:09.915 --> 00:06:12.575
And you can't stop me
from going to the festival.

134
00:06:12.585 --> 00:06:15.585
Mom already invited me.

135
00:06:15.588 --> 00:06:18.588
[horn blares]

136
00:06:18.591 --> 00:06:20.261
- [chuckles]

137
00:06:20.259 --> 00:06:21.529
So I walk up and say.

138
00:06:21.527 --> 00:06:24.227
"Looks like you had some car trouble.

139
00:06:24.230 --> 00:06:26.400
Good thing the police are here."

140
00:06:26.399 --> 00:06:29.129
- [laughs]
Did you write that beforehand?

141
00:06:29.135 --> 00:06:32.595
- Yeah. I had a few others.
Let's see. uh...

142
00:06:32.605 --> 00:06:36.605
"Looks like you guys should
put more 'try' in triad." huh?

143
00:06:36.609 --> 00:06:41.149
Or. "When you get to jail.
tell 'em Mako sent ya."

144
00:06:41.147 --> 00:06:42.747
- Ooh. I like that one.

145
00:06:42.748 --> 00:06:45.618
- Okay. I'll use that next time.

146
00:06:45.618 --> 00:06:47.418
Beifong says if I keep it up.

147
00:06:47.420 --> 00:06:48.920
I could make detective soon.

148
00:06:48.921 --> 00:06:50.761
- Oh. that sounds so fun.

149
00:06:50.756 --> 00:06:52.786
All I do is train all day.

150
00:06:52.792 --> 00:06:56.632
It's like Tenzin's totally
forgotten how I beat Amon.

151
00:06:56.629 --> 00:06:58.299
- Tenzin's just trying
to help you become

152
00:06:58.297 --> 00:07:00.367
the best Avatar you can be.

153
00:07:00.366 --> 00:07:02.166
- Of course
you'd take his side.

154
00:07:02.168 --> 00:07:03.898
- I'm not taking his side.
I'm just--

155
00:07:03.903 --> 00:07:08.413
- I'm gonna take a walk.

156
00:07:08.407 --> 00:07:10.977
- Why is it so much easier
to bust triads

157
00:07:10.976 --> 00:07:12.536
than it is to get through
one conversation

158
00:07:12.545 --> 00:07:17.545
with my girlfriend?

159
00:07:18.951 --> 00:07:20.991
- Kids: Gran-Gran!

160
00:07:20.986 --> 00:07:23.356
- Oh. you've all gotten so big.

161
00:07:23.356 --> 00:07:24.956
- We missed you. Aunt Kya.

162
00:07:24.957 --> 00:07:27.387
- Oh. I missed you too.

163
00:07:27.393 --> 00:07:30.203
Your father doesn't bring you
to visit nearly enough.

164
00:07:30.196 --> 00:07:32.356
He's probably scared
I'll beat him up

165
00:07:32.365 --> 00:07:33.425
like when we were kids.

166
00:07:33.432 --> 00:07:35.802
- I'm not scared of you...

167
00:07:35.801 --> 00:07:38.971
anymore.

168
00:07:38.971 --> 00:07:41.071
You remember Mako
- Sir.

169
00:07:41.073 --> 00:07:43.043
- I hope you're
not getting my daughter

170
00:07:43.042 --> 00:07:45.182
into any more trouble
up in the city.

171
00:07:45.177 --> 00:07:48.807
- Uh. no.
I. uh--no.

172
00:07:48.814 --> 00:07:51.884
- Knock it off. Dad.
- [chuckles]

173
00:07:51.884 --> 00:07:53.454
- Wow. look at all these people

174
00:07:53.452 --> 00:07:54.692
that came out to greet us.

175
00:07:54.687 --> 00:07:57.717
- Uh. no.
They came to greet them.

176
00:07:57.723 --> 00:08:01.893
[cheers and applause]

177
00:08:01.894 --> 00:08:05.064
- The great chief
of the Northern Water Tribe

178
00:08:05.064 --> 00:08:07.534
comes to grace us with his presence.

179
00:08:07.533 --> 00:08:09.003
[mockingly]
Hooray.

180
00:08:09.001 --> 00:08:10.441
- Just relax. Tonraq.

181
00:08:10.436 --> 00:08:12.266
He'll be gone soon enough.

182
00:08:12.271 --> 00:08:13.941
- [grumbles]

183
00:08:13.939 --> 00:08:18.939
[bird squawks]

184
00:08:21.647 --> 00:08:25.447
- Whoa. who are the lovely ladies?

185
00:08:25.451 --> 00:08:28.151
- That's Eska and Desna.
the chief's children.

186
00:08:28.154 --> 00:08:29.754
Desna is a guy.

187
00:08:29.755 --> 00:08:32.855
- [laughs] Oh. no. sure.
I knew that.

188
00:08:32.858 --> 00:08:36.628
And which one is Desna?

189
00:08:36.629 --> 00:08:39.299
- Good to see you again.
Avatar Korra.

190
00:08:39.298 --> 00:08:40.928
- Good to see you too.

191
00:08:40.933 --> 00:08:42.673
- Tonraq.

192
00:08:42.668 --> 00:08:47.668
- Brother.

193
00:08:53.245 --> 00:08:55.075
- It's a shame the Southerners
have abandoned

194
00:08:55.080 --> 00:08:57.050
all connections to the spirits.

195
00:08:57.049 --> 00:08:59.319
even during
the most hallowed times.

196
00:08:59.318 --> 00:09:01.548
- I've always loved
the Glacier Spirits Festival.

197
00:09:01.554 --> 00:09:03.124
It's fun.

198
00:09:03.122 --> 00:09:04.922
- This festival
used to be a solemn time

199
00:09:04.924 --> 00:09:06.864
of fasting and meditation.

200
00:09:06.859 --> 00:09:09.159
Now it's just a chance
to watch some rube

201
00:09:09.161 --> 00:09:13.131
try to stick an entire
arctic hen in his mouth.

202
00:09:13.132 --> 00:09:15.502
- [muffled]
Wha--what? It's so good.

203
00:09:15.501 --> 00:09:17.501
- Traditions change.

204
00:09:17.503 --> 00:09:20.143
It's not the end of the world.

205
00:09:20.139 --> 00:09:22.069
- Tell that to the sailors
who are being attacked

206
00:09:22.074 --> 00:09:24.784
by angry spirits in southern waters.

207
00:09:24.777 --> 00:09:26.977
Some traditions have purpose.

208
00:09:26.979 --> 00:09:30.979
- Wait. spirits are attacking ships?

209
00:09:30.983 --> 00:09:33.693
- I'm surprised the Avatar
doesn't know about that.

210
00:09:33.686 --> 00:09:35.316
Apparently you haven't been given

211
00:09:35.321 --> 00:09:36.961
all the information you need.

212
00:09:36.956 --> 00:09:39.116
It would be my honor to instruct you

213
00:09:39.124 --> 00:09:41.264
in the spiritual ways
of the Water Tribe.

214
00:09:41.260 --> 00:09:43.800
- I wouldn't mind learning
about fighting spirits.

215
00:09:43.796 --> 00:09:46.056
Airbending is getting pretty boring.

216
00:09:46.065 --> 00:09:47.925
- Tenzin is Korra's instructor.

217
00:09:47.933 --> 00:09:50.343
He can give her
all the training she needs.

218
00:09:50.336 --> 00:09:55.336
- So you've said.

219
00:09:56.442 --> 00:09:58.142
- I'm glad you came with me
to this meeting.

220
00:09:58.143 --> 00:10:00.813
Varrick is one of
the richest men in the world.

221
00:10:00.813 --> 00:10:04.153
and he controls the entire
global shipping business.

222
00:10:04.149 --> 00:10:06.179
So you're my assistant.

223
00:10:06.185 --> 00:10:08.285
Just stand there
and don't say anything.

224
00:10:08.287 --> 00:10:09.687
[Pabu chitters]
- No problem.

225
00:10:09.688 --> 00:10:12.018
Pabu and I are natural assistants.

226
00:10:12.024 --> 00:10:14.494
Man. this is nice.

227
00:10:14.493 --> 00:10:19.493
I gotta get into
this whole "business" thing.

228
00:10:24.136 --> 00:10:26.736
- Did you see that?
Levitation!

229
00:10:26.739 --> 00:10:29.309
[laughs]
I was a foot off the ground.

230
00:10:29.308 --> 00:10:30.678
Is that incredible or what?

231
00:10:30.676 --> 00:10:32.376
- How does he do that?

232
00:10:32.378 --> 00:10:34.048
- That's unbelievable.

233
00:10:34.046 --> 00:10:36.376
- What?

234
00:10:36.382 --> 00:10:37.822
It looked like you
were just sitting on a pillow.

235
00:10:37.816 --> 00:10:38.846
[Gasps]

236
00:10:38.851 --> 00:10:42.051
[all gasp]

237
00:10:42.054 --> 00:10:45.194
- Are you saying I wasn't levitating?

238
00:10:45.190 --> 00:10:49.030
- [gulps]
Uh.no?

239
00:10:49.028 --> 00:10:50.558
- Well. why didn't anyone tell me?

240
00:10:50.563 --> 00:10:51.863
Now I look like an idiot!

241
00:10:51.864 --> 00:10:56.864
Swami. you're fired!

242
00:11:00.439 --> 00:11:01.669
- Aah!
- I like you. kid.

243
00:11:01.674 --> 00:11:03.544
You're a real straight shooter.
just like me.

244
00:11:03.542 --> 00:11:05.782
Ms. Sato? He's with you?
- Mm-hmm.

245
00:11:05.778 --> 00:11:09.008
- Brought your tiger-shark
with you to do business. huh?

246
00:11:09.014 --> 00:11:11.354
Now that's moxie.
[laughs]

247
00:11:11.350 --> 00:11:13.220
Get over here and pop a squat.

248
00:11:13.218 --> 00:11:15.518
Zhu Li. get some tea for my guests.

249
00:11:15.521 --> 00:11:17.421
- Thank you for meeting with me.

250
00:11:17.423 --> 00:11:20.093
As you know. Future Industries
is looking for a partner

251
00:11:20.092 --> 00:11:21.532
to handle our shipping--
- Sure.

252
00:11:21.527 --> 00:11:22.787
But first. you gotta check out

253
00:11:22.795 --> 00:11:25.755
my new venture:
moving pictures.

254
00:11:25.764 --> 00:11:30.204
Zhu Li. do the thing.

255
00:11:30.202 --> 00:11:35.202
You're gonna love this.

256
00:11:38.344 --> 00:11:40.114
Mind-blowing. right?

257
00:11:40.112 --> 00:11:42.552
- Yeah.
- Now. forget that!

258
00:11:42.548 --> 00:11:45.378
That's the past!
Shut it off. Zhu Li!

259
00:11:45.384 --> 00:11:47.154
Imagine watching this.

260
00:11:47.152 --> 00:11:49.052
Ginger. come over here
and do your poses.

261
00:11:49.054 --> 00:11:51.064
- [gasps]

262
00:11:51.056 --> 00:11:54.056
[Sultry music]

263
00:11:56.895 --> 00:11:58.625
- Spectacular.

264
00:11:58.631 --> 00:12:00.131
And we tell a story.

265
00:12:00.132 --> 00:12:01.602
There's romance. action.

266
00:12:01.600 --> 00:12:03.270
some funny animal stuff
for the kids.

267
00:12:03.268 --> 00:12:04.338
You know. whatever.

268
00:12:04.336 --> 00:12:06.736
Thanks. Ginger.
Go rest your gams.

269
00:12:06.739 --> 00:12:09.539
How about that. tiger-shark?

270
00:12:09.541 --> 00:12:10.811
We're gonna do big business

271
00:12:10.809 --> 00:12:13.209
with these "movers."
as I call 'em.

272
00:12:13.212 --> 00:12:14.982
- Okay.

273
00:12:14.980 --> 00:12:16.150
But I'm just concentrating

274
00:12:16.148 --> 00:12:18.248
on getting Future Industries
back on track.

275
00:12:18.250 --> 00:12:19.520
If we could hammer out a deal--

276
00:12:19.518 --> 00:12:20.988
. StOP-

277
00:12:20.986 --> 00:12:25.986
Look me in the eye.

278
00:12:27.459 --> 00:12:29.459
We got a deal!

279
00:12:29.461 --> 00:12:33.561
[all cheering]

280
00:12:33.565 --> 00:12:36.695
We'll hammer out the details
at the royal feast tonight.

281
00:12:36.702 --> 00:12:39.602
Now who wants
a rocket-boat ride?

282
00:12:39.605 --> 00:12:43.605
[all cheering]

283
00:12:43.609 --> 00:12:47.249
- Is that how business
usually goes?

284
00:12:47.246 --> 00:12:52.246
- You are a natural assistant.

285
00:12:54.486 --> 00:12:57.286
- This is a wonderful feast
in your honor. Uncle.

286
00:12:57.289 --> 00:12:58.919
- This is nothing.

287
00:12:58.924 --> 00:13:00.434
When this festival was founded.

288
00:13:00.426 --> 00:13:02.826
the tribal elders would commune
with the spirits.

289
00:13:02.828 --> 00:13:05.298
People would watch
the brilliant displays of light

290
00:13:05.297 --> 00:13:07.097
as spirits danced in the sky.

291
00:13:07.099 --> 00:13:09.599
- Wow.
I've never seen that.

292
00:13:09.601 --> 00:13:11.271
- And that is a shame.

293
00:13:11.270 --> 00:13:12.870
since the Avatar is the bridge

294
00:13:12.871 --> 00:13:15.571
between the material world
and the spirits.

295
00:13:15.574 --> 00:13:18.414
That is why I want so badly
to teach you.

296
00:13:18.410 --> 00:13:20.210
to help you fulfill your destiny.

297
00:13:20.212 --> 00:13:22.212
- I thought I had made it clear

298
00:13:22.214 --> 00:13:25.384
that Tenzin is teaching her.

299
00:13:25.384 --> 00:13:29.094
- Every Avatar before you
traveled the world to learn.

300
00:13:29.088 --> 00:13:31.988
It was Tenzin and your father
who kept you secluded

301
00:13:31.990 --> 00:13:33.290
at the South Pole.

302
00:13:33.292 --> 00:13:35.492
- I thought Aang
ordered the White Lotus

303
00:13:35.494 --> 00:13:37.804
to keep me down here?

304
00:13:37.796 --> 00:13:40.356
- We all did what
we thought was best for you.

305
00:13:40.365 --> 00:13:43.365
- Who I train with
should be my decision. Dad.

306
00:13:43.368 --> 00:13:47.068
not yours or Tenzin's.

307
00:13:47.072 --> 00:13:48.972
- Looks like someone's
trying to take your place

308
00:13:48.974 --> 00:13:51.784
as the Avatar's
stick-in-the-mud mentor.

309
00:13:51.777 --> 00:13:53.577
- Bumi. don't pick on Tenzin.

310
00:13:53.579 --> 00:13:55.509
You know he's always been sensitive.

311
00:13:55.514 --> 00:13:57.854
- I'm not sensitive!

312
00:13:57.850 --> 00:14:02.590
[both laughing]

313
00:14:02.588 --> 00:14:05.018
- As your chief.
it is my honor to speak

314
00:14:05.023 --> 00:14:07.293
at this festival.
which was founded

315
00:14:07.292 --> 00:14:09.092
to bring our tribes together

316
00:14:09.094 --> 00:14:10.804
and restore the ancient balance

317
00:14:10.796 --> 00:14:13.696
between our world
and that of the spirits.

318
00:14:13.699 --> 00:14:17.599
But I am saddened to see
what it has become--

319
00:14:17.603 --> 00:14:21.543
a cheap carnival that celebrates
greedy and trivial humans.

320
00:14:21.540 --> 00:14:23.140
- [teeth squeaking]

321
00:14:23.142 --> 00:14:25.382
- I fear the time is fast approaching

322
00:14:25.377 --> 00:14:28.277
when the North can no longer
stand idly by

323
00:14:28.280 --> 00:14:32.720
while our Southern brothers
slip into total spiritual decay.

324
00:14:32.718 --> 00:14:34.988
Angry spirits are already
attacking ships

325
00:14:34.987 --> 00:14:36.217
in your waters.

326
00:14:36.221 --> 00:14:38.821
I only hope we are not too late

327
00:14:38.824 --> 00:14:40.634
to change course.

328
00:14:40.626 --> 00:14:43.926
[all murmuring]

329
00:14:43.929 --> 00:14:45.659
- Chief Unalaq. everybody.

330
00:14:45.664 --> 00:14:46.904
Always great to have him in town.

331
00:14:46.899 --> 00:14:48.229
Now let's have some fun

332
00:14:48.233 --> 00:14:51.303
with Wacky Wushu's
dancin' otter-penguins.

333
00:14:51.303 --> 00:14:54.313
[energetic music]

334
00:14:59.812 --> 00:15:02.812
[carnival music]

335
00:15:02.815 --> 00:15:05.815
- [Giggles]

336
00:15:05.818 --> 00:15:10.818
- Mm-mm.

337
00:15:13.659 --> 00:15:15.459
- [clears throat]

338
00:15:15.460 --> 00:15:18.730
Wish me luck.
I'm making my move.

339
00:15:18.730 --> 00:15:20.130
Whee!

340
00:15:20.132 --> 00:15:21.432
- Good luck.

341
00:15:21.433 --> 00:15:23.533
- Those two
have always creeped me out.

342
00:15:23.535 --> 00:15:25.765
They smell like a grandma's attic.

343
00:15:25.771 --> 00:15:28.841
- Hey. I'm Bolin.
I'm a friend of Korra's.

344
00:15:28.841 --> 00:15:30.271
You're Eska. right?

345
00:15:30.275 --> 00:15:33.275
Wow. I'm just--
I'm loving these robes.

346
00:15:33.278 --> 00:15:34.778
- [hisses]

347
00:15:34.780 --> 00:15:36.710
- [clears throat]

348
00:15:36.715 --> 00:15:40.615
So you are from the North.
right? Cool.

349
00:15:40.619 --> 00:15:42.789
That's like-- you know. that's. like.
my favorite direction.

350
00:15:42.788 --> 00:15:44.888
- I think he is trying to establish

351
00:15:44.890 --> 00:15:46.290
some kind of bond with you

352
00:15:46.291 --> 00:15:48.661
based on your geographic
point of origin.

353
00:15:48.660 --> 00:15:50.160
- Perhaps it would be interesting

354
00:15:50.162 --> 00:15:51.632
to spend time with a person

355
00:15:51.630 --> 00:15:54.330
whose ways are so rough
and uncultured.

356
00:15:54.333 --> 00:15:57.103
You amuse me.
I will make you mine.

357
00:15:57.102 --> 00:16:00.672
- You mean like a boyfriend
or--or like a slave?

358
00:16:00.672 --> 00:16:02.312
- Yes.

359
00:16:02.307 --> 00:16:07.307
Win me prizes.
- [laughs nervously]

360
00:16:07.980 --> 00:16:09.010
[bell dings]

361
00:16:09.014 --> 00:16:10.624
- Unalaq offered to train me.

362
00:16:10.616 --> 00:16:12.376
He says he can teach me
about the spirits

363
00:16:12.384 --> 00:16:13.484
and my connection to them.

364
00:16:13.485 --> 00:16:16.615
- Sounds good.
What does Tenzin think?

365
00:16:16.622 --> 00:16:18.492
- Tenzin thinks I'm his prisoner

366
00:16:18.490 --> 00:16:19.890
or one of his kids.

367
00:16:19.892 --> 00:16:24.502
I'll never finish training
with him in charge.

368
00:16:24.496 --> 00:16:25.526
[bell dings]

369
00:16:25.530 --> 00:16:28.370
- We have a winner.

370
00:16:28.367 --> 00:16:30.867
- I mean. you heard what Unalaq said.

371
00:16:30.869 --> 00:16:32.999
The South is spiritually unbalanced.

372
00:16:33.005 --> 00:16:35.235
and it's the Avatar's job to fix it.

373
00:16:35.240 --> 00:16:36.270
But my dad won't even let me

374
00:16:36.275 --> 00:16:39.175
think about Unalaq teaching me.

375
00:16:39.177 --> 00:16:40.577
Well?
- Well. what?

376
00:16:40.579 --> 00:16:42.579
- What do you think I should do?

377
00:16:42.581 --> 00:16:44.581
- I guess you should do
what you think is right.

378
00:16:44.583 --> 00:16:47.023
I support whatever decision you make.

379
00:16:47.019 --> 00:16:49.849
- Oh. thanks.
That's a big help.

380
00:16:49.855 --> 00:16:52.255
- I thought you wanted me
to be supportive.

381
00:16:52.257 --> 00:16:54.357
Now you want me
to tell you what I think?

382
00:16:54.359 --> 00:16:55.629
Make up your mind.

383
00:16:55.627 --> 00:16:57.527
Qof!

384
00:16:57.529 --> 00:17:02.529
- Just forget it.

385
00:17:05.771 --> 00:17:10.771
[bells chiming]

386
00:17:11.276 --> 00:17:12.776
Ugh.

387
00:17:12.778 --> 00:17:14.008
Naga. what are you doing?

388
00:17:14.012 --> 00:17:15.052
[Naga howling]

389
00:17:15.047 --> 00:17:16.877
Naga.hush.

390
00:17:16.882 --> 00:17:21.882
[howling continues]

391
00:17:22.521 --> 00:17:24.961
Quiet. Naga.
You'll wake everyone up.

392
00:17:24.957 --> 00:17:27.017
[Naga howling]

393
00:17:27.025 --> 00:17:32.025
- [yawns]
What's going on?

394
00:17:33.298 --> 00:17:37.898
- What is that?

395
00:17:37.903 --> 00:17:39.273
Ugh!

396
00:17:39.271 --> 00:17:44.271
[groans]

397
00:17:44.476 --> 00:17:49.306
[spirit growls]

398
00:17:48.314 --> 00:17:53.314
[groans]

399
00:17:53.853 --> 00:17:56.863
- Got it!

400
00:17:56.856 --> 00:17:57.886
Don't got it!

401
00:17:57.890 --> 00:18:02.890
[both groaning]

402
00:18:16.609 --> 00:18:21.609
- Korra!

403
00:18:28.321 --> 00:18:30.191
Aah!

404
00:18:30.189 --> 00:18:31.859
[screams]

405
00:18:31.858 --> 00:18:33.858
[groans]

406
00:18:33.860 --> 00:18:35.990
- Aah!

407
00:18:35.995 --> 00:18:40.995
[groans]

408
00:18:44.437 --> 00:18:47.107
- Spirit. why are you angry with us?

409
00:18:47.106 --> 00:18:51.906
What have we done to offend you?

410
00:18:51.911 --> 00:18:56.911
[groans]

411
00:19:19.272 --> 00:19:21.512
-[Grunts]

412
00:19:21.507 --> 00:19:26.507
[groans]

413
00:20:11.557 --> 00:20:16.557
- Go in peace.

414
00:20:18.464 --> 00:20:21.634
- Korra. are you all right?

415
00:20:21.634 --> 00:20:23.304
- How were you able
to control that spirit

416
00:20:23.302 --> 00:20:24.402
when no one else could?

417
00:20:24.403 --> 00:20:25.943
- As your father could tell you.

418
00:20:25.938 --> 00:20:28.208
I have spent my life
studying the spirits

419
00:20:28.207 --> 00:20:30.007
and learning their ways.

420
00:20:30.009 --> 00:20:32.279
All of this knowledge
is lost in the South.

421
00:20:32.278 --> 00:20:35.308
but I could teach you
everything I know.

422
00:20:35.314 --> 00:20:38.754
- Chief Unalaq. clearly.
you are very knowledgeable.

423
00:20:38.751 --> 00:20:41.451
but Korra still has much
to learn about airbending.

424
00:20:41.454 --> 00:20:44.164
and I hope that going
to the Air Temples

425
00:20:44.157 --> 00:20:46.587
will help her connect
with the past Avatars.

426
00:20:46.592 --> 00:20:47.832
- Ugh!

427
00:20:47.827 --> 00:20:49.927
- The Air Temples
will teach her nothing.

428
00:20:49.929 --> 00:20:52.329
Only I can give her
the training she needs

429
00:20:52.331 --> 00:20:54.771
to be a complete Avatar.

430
00:20:54.767 --> 00:20:56.937
- I've told you that will not happen.

431
00:20:56.936 --> 00:20:58.566
- Hey. I'm right here!

432
00:20:58.571 --> 00:21:00.741
Anyone want to ask me what I think?

433
00:21:00.740 --> 00:21:02.310
- Korra. please. listen.

434
00:21:02.308 --> 00:21:04.838
- I'm tired of listening
to you-- both of you.

435
00:21:04.844 --> 00:21:06.554
You keep me locked up.

436
00:21:06.546 --> 00:21:08.076
telling me you know what's best.

437
00:21:08.080 --> 00:21:09.480
but both of you were powerless

438
00:21:09.482 --> 00:21:12.452
against the spirit attack.

439
00:21:12.451 --> 00:21:16.961
I think it's time I had a new teacher.

440
00:21:16.956 --> 00:21:18.556
- Now. Korra--

441
00:21:18.558 --> 00:21:19.928
- Unalaq has proven he's the only one

442
00:21:19.926 --> 00:21:23.626
who knows what I need to learn.

443
00:21:23.629 --> 00:21:25.029
I have to go with him.

444
00:21:25.031 --> 00:21:27.471
- Please. I know you're angry.

445
00:21:27.466 --> 00:21:30.896
but we've come so far together.

446
00:21:30.903 --> 00:21:32.303
- I'm sorry. Tenzin.

447
00:21:32.305 --> 00:21:37.305
This is as far as we go.

448
00:21:38.911 --> 00:21:41.151
- It has been a pleasure serving you.

449
00:21:41.147 --> 00:21:46.147
Avatar Korra.

450
00:21:53.559 --> 00:21:57.399
- I think you forgot a couple of things.

451
00:21:57.396 --> 00:22:00.326
- Mother. I think I need some time alone

452
00:22:00.333 --> 00:22:01.703
with my family right now.

453
00:22:01.701 --> 00:22:04.001
- This is your family. Tenzin.

454
00:22:04.003 --> 00:22:05.373
When you get to be my age.

455
00:22:05.371 --> 00:22:07.241
you'll be thankful for the time you had

456
00:22:07.240 --> 00:22:08.610
with your siblings.

457
00:22:08.608 --> 00:22:11.008
Besides. I think it's important

458
00:22:11.010 --> 00:22:14.550
that you all visit
your father's home together.

459
00:22:14.547 --> 00:22:16.507
- Come on. it'll be fun.

460
00:22:16.515 --> 00:22:19.445
- I'm dying to see that
laid-back "Vacation Tenzin"

461
00:22:19.452 --> 00:22:20.992
I've heard so much about.

462
00:22:20.987 --> 00:22:25.257
- All right.
Hop on.

463
00:22:25.258 --> 00:22:27.228
I love you. Mom.

464
00:22:27.226 --> 00:22:28.686
We'll see you soon.

465
00:22:28.694 --> 00:22:33.694
- [grunts]
Oh!

466
00:22:39.105 --> 00:22:41.435
- Do you think I did the right thing?

467
00:22:41.440 --> 00:22:43.540
- [sighs]
I don't know.

468
00:22:43.542 --> 00:22:45.542
I'm sorry.
but I'm not very good

469
00:22:45.544 --> 00:22:47.914
at this Avatar counseling thing.

470
00:22:47.913 --> 00:22:50.053
But I know your heart
is in the right place.

471
00:22:50.049 --> 00:22:55.049
You'll just have to trust it.

472
00:22:59.125 --> 00:23:01.385
- I know this was
a hard decision. Korra.

473
00:23:01.394 --> 00:23:03.304
But it was the right one.

474
00:23:03.296 --> 00:23:05.056
Now it is time to put it behind you

475
00:23:05.064 --> 00:23:06.804
and begin your new training.

476
00:23:06.799 --> 00:23:11.799
I have great plans for you.

477
00:23:17.376 --> 00:23:20.376
[gentle instrumental music]

478
00:23:28.376 --> 00:23:29.256
- You're early.

479
00:23:29.760 --> 00:23:31.030
- What can I say?

480
00:23:31.028 --> 00:23:33.898
I'm pumped up to learn
that Unalaq spirit fighting.

481
00:23:33.898 --> 00:23:36.298
- I'm not here to teach you
to fight spirits.

482
00:23:36.300 --> 00:23:38.640
I'm here to help you
begin your spiritual training.

483
00:23:38.636 --> 00:23:41.836
We're going to one of the most
remote places in the world--

484
00:23:41.839 --> 00:23:45.009
the long-neglected
spiritual center of your tribe:

485
00:23:45.009 --> 00:23:46.249
the South Pole.

486
00:23:46.244 --> 00:23:48.674
- You're gonna train me
at the South Pole?

487
00:23:48.679 --> 00:23:50.919
- We will do more than just train.

488
00:23:50.915 --> 00:23:53.185
By neglecting the spirits.
the people of the South

489
00:23:53.184 --> 00:23:55.114
have brought darkness
upon themselves.

490
00:23:55.119 --> 00:23:58.329
and now it threatens
to destroy our tribe.

491
00:23:58.322 --> 00:24:00.152
We must set things right.

492
00:24:00.158 --> 00:24:03.328
The Southern Water Tribe
depends on you.

493
00:24:03.327 --> 00:24:05.327
- A dangerous trip to the South Pole?

494
00:24:05.329 --> 00:24:10.329
Count me in.

495
00:24:11.969 --> 00:24:15.179
- There it is.
the Southern Air Temple.

496
00:24:15.173 --> 00:24:20.173
Isn't it magnificent?

497
00:24:23.147 --> 00:24:27.087
- Master Tenzin. welcome.

498
00:24:27.084 --> 00:24:29.684
- Good to see you again.
Abbot Shung.

499
00:24:29.687 --> 00:24:31.057
- Is there anything you need?

500
00:24:31.055 --> 00:24:33.085
Water?
Dandelion greens?

501
00:24:33.090 --> 00:24:35.300
Ah. perhaps you'd like
to re-center yourself

502
00:24:35.293 --> 00:24:37.293
by meditating in the gardens.

503
00:24:37.295 --> 00:24:38.595
- No. thank you.

504
00:24:38.596 --> 00:24:39.626
I'm fine.

505
00:24:39.630 --> 00:24:41.940
- And you must
be the honorable Pema.

506
00:24:41.933 --> 00:24:43.563
Please. accept these gifts.

507
00:24:43.568 --> 00:24:46.808
This is an ancient
Airbender head shaver

508
00:24:46.804 --> 00:24:49.074
we've refurbished just for you.

509
00:24:49.073 --> 00:24:51.643
- Oh...okay.

510
00:24:51.642 --> 00:24:56.042
- And Pema. these flowers
once filled the mountainside.

511
00:24:56.047 --> 00:24:58.647
Now they can brighten up your room.

512
00:24:58.649 --> 00:25:00.819
- That's...sweet?

513
00:25:00.818 --> 00:25:02.718
You didn't have to.

514
00:25:02.720 --> 00:25:04.230
- Nonsense.

515
00:25:04.222 --> 00:25:05.782
Whatever you need is yours.

516
00:25:05.790 --> 00:25:06.960
Anything for the mother

517
00:25:06.958 --> 00:25:09.158
of the next generation of Airbenders.

518
00:25:09.160 --> 00:25:11.670
- No! That gift is mine.

519
00:25:11.662 --> 00:25:13.092
- You don't even like to read.

520
00:25:13.097 --> 00:25:14.737
- Naah.

521
00:25:14.732 --> 00:25:18.262
- Yep. those are the world's
next generation of Airbenders.

522
00:25:18.269 --> 00:25:19.809
- Mommy. Daddy. look.

523
00:25:19.804 --> 00:25:21.204
I finally got a lemur.

524
00:25:21.205 --> 00:25:23.875
I'm gonna name him Poki.

525
00:25:23.874 --> 00:25:28.314
Poki. come back!

526
00:25:28.312 --> 00:25:30.812
- Ugh.

527
00:25:30.815 --> 00:25:31.915
Phew.

528
00:25:31.916 --> 00:25:33.286
Excuse me. a little help here.

529
00:25:33.284 --> 00:25:36.784
- Sorry. I thought
you were the servants.

530
00:25:36.787 --> 00:25:38.887
- We're Tenzin's brother and sister.

531
00:25:38.889 --> 00:25:41.159
- Avatar Aang had other children?

532
00:25:41.158 --> 00:25:43.598
The world is filled
with more Airbenders?

533
00:25:43.594 --> 00:25:45.024
- We're not Airbenders.

534
00:25:45.029 --> 00:25:50.029
- Oh.
I'm so sorry.

535
00:25:53.237 --> 00:25:56.037
- I thought you said Bolin was coming.

536
00:25:56.040 --> 00:25:58.780
- He said he'd be here.
but I can't worry about it.

537
00:25:58.776 --> 00:26:00.676
I have to make sure
you have everything you need

538
00:26:00.678 --> 00:26:01.948
for a safe trip.

539
00:26:01.946 --> 00:26:04.586
- Thanks. Captain Expedition.
but I'll be fine.

540
00:26:04.582 --> 00:26:09.582
[engine hums]

541
00:26:12.590 --> 00:26:14.830
- Tonraq. what do you want?

542
00:26:14.825 --> 00:26:16.825
- I heard you're taking
Korra to the South Pole.

543
00:26:16.827 --> 00:26:18.027
I'm coming.

544
00:26:18.029 --> 00:26:19.129
- Absolutely not.

545
00:26:19.130 --> 00:26:20.830
You're a distraction to Korra

546
00:26:20.831 --> 00:26:22.791
and a hindrance
to what needs to be done.

547
00:26:22.800 --> 00:26:24.940
- My daughter is not going without me.

548
00:26:24.935 --> 00:26:27.035
She needs someone
to watch after her.

549
00:26:27.038 --> 00:26:30.138
- Dad. why do you always think
you know what's best for me?

550
00:26:30.141 --> 00:26:32.741
- Because he's misguided.

551
00:26:32.743 --> 00:26:34.873
The sad truth is
it's men like your father

552
00:26:34.879 --> 00:26:37.119
who have put the spirit world
out of balance.

553
00:26:37.114 --> 00:26:38.744
He's ignored my warnings in the past

554
00:26:38.749 --> 00:26:40.289
and hasn't learned since.

555
00:26:40.284 --> 00:26:42.084
- What happened in the past?

556
00:26:42.086 --> 00:26:43.756
- It doesn't matter.

557
00:26:43.754 --> 00:26:45.224
What matters is the Everstorm.

558
00:26:45.222 --> 00:26:46.652
- The Everstorm?

559
00:26:46.657 --> 00:26:47.897
- It's a massive blizzard

560
00:26:47.892 --> 00:26:50.292
that's battered
the South Pole for decades.

561
00:26:50.294 --> 00:26:55.294
I'm coming.
unless you think you can stop me.

562
00:26:58.135 --> 00:27:03.135
- Guys!
Hey. wait for me!

563
00:27:06.277 --> 00:27:07.607
Check it out.

564
00:27:07.611 --> 00:27:09.241
I'm traveling in style.
[engine revs]

565
00:27:09.246 --> 00:27:11.646
Whoa!
Okay. I'm sorry.

566
00:27:11.649 --> 00:27:13.619
Still getting used to that throttle.

567
00:27:13.617 --> 00:27:15.287
- Uh. where'd you get the ride?

568
00:27:15.286 --> 00:27:16.956
- Varrick.
He's awesome.

569
00:27:16.954 --> 00:27:18.354
He also gave me
this fancy snowsuit.

570
00:27:18.356 --> 00:27:20.156
It's inflatable
with an internal heater.

571
00:27:20.157 --> 00:27:22.327
emergency beacon.
and food ration pouch.

572
00:27:22.326 --> 00:27:24.296
I mean. if I get lost.
I can survive in this thing

573
00:27:24.295 --> 00:27:25.865
for. like. like. a month.

574
00:27:25.863 --> 00:27:27.693
Who wants some freeze-dried
cucumber-quats?

575
00:27:27.698 --> 00:27:29.068
Nobody?

576
00:27:29.066 --> 00:27:31.566
Did I interrupt a conversation?

577
00:27:31.569 --> 00:27:32.739
[Pabu squeaks]

578
00:27:32.737 --> 00:27:34.977
- No. the conversation is over.

579
00:27:34.972 --> 00:27:36.672
Dad. come if you want.

580
00:27:36.674 --> 00:27:40.704
Just don't interfere with my training.

581
00:27:40.711 --> 00:27:44.071
- Does this sidecar have
the capacity for two passengers?

582
00:27:44.081 --> 00:27:45.581
- Sure does.

583
00:27:45.583 --> 00:27:48.283
But. uh. who's gonna drive?

584
00:27:48.285 --> 00:27:53.285
[engine humming]

585
00:27:54.625 --> 00:27:56.155
- Well. what do you know?

586
00:27:56.160 --> 00:27:58.730
Looks like--
- Go away. Mako.

587
00:27:58.729 --> 00:28:02.299
- So once we get to the South Pole.
then what happens?

588
00:28:02.299 --> 00:28:04.669
- You will open
an ancient spirit portal.

589
00:28:04.668 --> 00:28:06.808
- I'm sorry.
What now?

590
00:28:06.804 --> 00:28:08.804
- At the South Pole.
there is a portal

591
00:28:08.806 --> 00:28:11.306
that connects our world
to the spirit world.

592
00:28:11.308 --> 00:28:13.608
But it has long been closed.

593
00:28:13.611 --> 00:28:15.341
- And that's why
the evil spirits are attacking?

594
00:28:15.346 --> 00:28:17.576
- There are no evil spirits.
[lightning cracks]

595
00:28:17.581 --> 00:28:21.041
There is light and dark in them all.

596
00:28:21.051 --> 00:28:24.881
But when they're unbalanced.
the darkness takes over.

597
00:28:24.889 --> 00:28:26.629
If you can open the portal in time.

598
00:28:26.624 --> 00:28:28.994
balance will be restored.

599
00:28:28.993 --> 00:28:30.953
- What do you mean "in time"?

600
00:28:30.961 --> 00:28:33.221
- There's a reason
the Glacier Spirits Festival

601
00:28:33.230 --> 00:28:34.940
ends on the winter solstice.

602
00:28:34.932 --> 00:28:36.692
That's when the spirit world

603
00:28:36.700 --> 00:28:38.810
and the physical world
are close together.

604
00:28:38.803 --> 00:28:42.273
Only then can the Avatar
open the portal.

605
00:28:42.273 --> 00:28:44.033
- The winter solstice is tomorrow.

606
00:28:44.041 --> 00:28:45.301
- Exactly.

607
00:28:45.309 --> 00:28:50.309
And we can't afford
to wait another year.

608
00:28:50.481 --> 00:28:54.981
[spirit hisses]

609
00:28:54.985 --> 00:28:57.185
[growls]

610
00:28:57.188 --> 00:29:02.188
- Easy. Naga.
[continues growling]

611
00:29:04.562 --> 00:29:06.992
- What are those?

612
00:29:06.997 --> 00:29:11.997
- Dark spirits.

613
00:29:13.037 --> 00:29:14.337
- Let's keep moving.

614
00:29:14.338 --> 00:29:19.338
We have to find
a safe place to set up camp.

615
00:29:25.049 --> 00:29:26.119
- Uncle. why do you think
the dark spirits

616
00:29:26.116 --> 00:29:27.286
are following us?

617
00:29:27.284 --> 00:29:29.984
- Can we not talk
about dark spirits. please?

618
00:29:29.987 --> 00:29:31.727
- My brother doesn't like ghost stories.

619
00:29:31.722 --> 00:29:33.022
- Don't worry.

620
00:29:33.023 --> 00:29:34.993
I will protect you.
my feeble turtle-duck.

621
00:29:34.992 --> 00:29:36.052
- Thank you.

622
00:29:36.060 --> 00:29:38.630
- Sadly. this isn't a ghost story.

623
00:29:38.629 --> 00:29:40.229
This is real.

624
00:29:40.231 --> 00:29:41.631
- [gasps]

625
00:29:41.632 --> 00:29:44.092
- The spirits are angry
because he's here.

626
00:29:44.101 --> 00:29:46.061
Haven't you ever wondered
how your father

627
00:29:46.070 --> 00:29:48.240
ended up in the South Pole?

628
00:29:48.239 --> 00:29:51.009
Why he's never taken you
to visit his homeland in the north?

629
00:29:51.008 --> 00:29:53.308
- Unalaq. this is not the time.

630
00:29:53.310 --> 00:29:55.120
- You're right.

631
00:29:55.112 --> 00:29:57.212
You should have told her
a long time ago.

632
00:29:57.214 --> 00:29:59.844
- Told me what?

633
00:29:59.850 --> 00:30:02.690
- I left the North Pole because...

634
00:30:02.686 --> 00:30:07.686
I was banished.

635
00:30:07.892 --> 00:30:10.752
- You were banished from the North? Why?

636
00:30:10.761 --> 00:30:14.931
- Because I almost destroyed
the entire tribe.

637
00:30:14.932 --> 00:30:17.902
20 years ago. I was a general
in the Northern Water Tribe.

638
00:30:17.902 --> 00:30:22.902
sworn to protect my people.

639
00:30:25.243 --> 00:30:30.243
- Brother. we're being attacked.

640
00:30:31.816 --> 00:30:34.716
[pained grunts]

641
00:30:34.719 --> 00:30:39.719
[scattered screaming]

642
00:30:41.159 --> 00:30:44.369
[water rushing]

643
00:30:44.362 --> 00:30:47.492
Tonraq: I drove them out of the city
and deep into the frozen tundra.

644
00:30:47.498 --> 00:30:52.498
[battle cries]

645
00:31:08.152 --> 00:31:13.152
We tracked them deep
into an ancient forest.

646
00:31:16.460 --> 00:31:19.600
Many believed this forest
was the home to spirits.

647
00:31:19.597 --> 00:31:21.267
and the barbarians retreated there

648
00:31:21.265 --> 00:31:22.365
because they thought we wouldn't attack

649
00:31:22.366 --> 00:31:25.336
on such hallowed grounds.

650
00:31:25.336 --> 00:31:29.106
They thought wrong.

651
00:31:29.106 --> 00:31:34.106
[all scream]

652
00:31:35.146 --> 00:31:37.246
- [grunts]

653
00:31:37.248 --> 00:31:38.848
- We captured the barbarians.

654
00:31:38.849 --> 00:31:43.849
but in the process.
we destroyed the forest.

655
00:31:47.291 --> 00:31:49.151
I didn't realize the consequences

656
00:31:49.160 --> 00:31:50.330
of what I had done.

657
00:31:50.328 --> 00:31:52.328
[monstrous hissing]

658
00:31:52.330 --> 00:31:54.200
By destroying the forest.

659
00:31:54.198 --> 00:31:58.708
I unknowingly let loose angry spirits.

660
00:31:58.703 --> 00:32:03.703
[both scream]

661
00:32:04.809 --> 00:32:07.209
They threatened to destroy everything.

662
00:32:07.211 --> 00:32:12.211
The entire city.

663
00:32:27.365 --> 00:32:30.335
Unalaq was able to guide
the spirits back to the forest.

664
00:32:30.334 --> 00:32:35.334
but by then.
the damage had been done.

665
00:32:43.047 --> 00:32:45.917
For being the cause
of so much devastation.

666
00:32:45.916 --> 00:32:48.316
my father banished me
from the Northern Water Tribe

667
00:32:48.319 --> 00:32:53.319
in shame.

668
00:32:55.693 --> 00:33:00.693
That's when I came to the South
and started a new life.

669
00:33:04.669 --> 00:33:05.939
- Whoa.

670
00:33:05.936 --> 00:33:08.736
So you were supposed to be chief.

671
00:33:08.739 --> 00:33:10.809
then he became chief.

672
00:33:10.808 --> 00:33:12.548
No wonder you guys
don't like each other.

673
00:33:12.543 --> 00:33:14.643
Ow! What?

674
00:33:14.645 --> 00:33:16.275
Isn't that what happened?

675
00:33:16.280 --> 00:33:18.450
- I can't believe
you kept this from me.

676
00:33:18.449 --> 00:33:20.289
- I was protecting you from the shame

677
00:33:20.284 --> 00:33:21.654
I brought on the family.

678
00:33:21.652 --> 00:33:23.482
- Why do you keep hiding things from me

679
00:33:23.487 --> 00:33:25.457
and then telling me
it's for my own protection?

680
00:33:25.456 --> 00:33:28.456
I'm tired of you protecting me.

681
00:33:28.459 --> 00:33:33.459
- Korra.

682
00:33:40.304 --> 00:33:41.774
Jinora: Wow.

683
00:33:41.772 --> 00:33:43.232
The statue room.

684
00:33:43.240 --> 00:33:45.410
- That's right. Jinora.

685
00:33:45.409 --> 00:33:49.519
The most sacred place in
the entire Southern Air Temple.

686
00:33:49.513 --> 00:33:54.483
Here you will find statues
of every Avatar who ever lived.

687
00:33:54.485 --> 00:33:57.355
Where are your brother and sister?

688
00:33:57.355 --> 00:33:59.755
[excited shouts]

689
00:33:59.757 --> 00:34:01.397
- You can't catch me.

690
00:34:01.392 --> 00:34:03.722
I'm the greatest air skater of all time.

691
00:34:03.728 --> 00:34:04.768
Qof!

692
00:34:04.762 --> 00:34:09.762
[rock crumbles]
- Meelo!

693
00:34:40.564 --> 00:34:43.364
- Korra. you have every right
to be mad at me.

694
00:34:43.367 --> 00:34:46.707
but I don't want you to make
the same mistake I made.

695
00:34:46.704 --> 00:34:49.234
I should have never
gone into that forest.

696
00:34:49.240 --> 00:34:52.210
and we shouldn't be going
to the South Pole now.

697
00:34:52.209 --> 00:34:57.209
Spirits and the physical world
should remain separate.

698
00:34:57.314 --> 00:34:59.244
- Dad. it's my job to be the bridge

699
00:34:59.250 --> 00:35:01.190
between the spirits
and the physical world.

700
00:35:01.185 --> 00:35:04.185
and I finally have a chance
to live up to my potential.

701
00:35:04.188 --> 00:35:06.328
- You don't even know
if what Unalaq says is true.

702
00:35:06.323 --> 00:35:07.523
- You want proof?

703
00:35:07.525 --> 00:35:08.955
Look to the sky.

704
00:35:08.959 --> 00:35:11.529
Where I'm from.
the spirits are at peace

705
00:35:11.529 --> 00:35:12.929
and they light up the dark.

706
00:35:12.930 --> 00:35:14.770
- The Northern lights.

707
00:35:14.765 --> 00:35:16.535
- Yes.

708
00:35:16.534 --> 00:35:18.764
There used to be lights
in the South as well.

709
00:35:18.769 --> 00:35:20.339
But during the 100 Year War.

710
00:35:20.337 --> 00:35:21.937
the South was thrown out of balance

711
00:35:21.939 --> 00:35:23.509
and the lights disappeared.

712
00:35:23.507 --> 00:35:25.377
When the war ended.
the North helped

713
00:35:25.376 --> 00:35:27.606
to rebuild you physically as a nation.

714
00:35:27.611 --> 00:35:30.341
But we have not rebuilt you spiritually.

715
00:35:30.347 --> 00:35:32.887
Now the spirits
no longer dance in your skies.

716
00:35:32.883 --> 00:35:36.513
Instead.
they rampage in the Everstorm.

717
00:35:36.520 --> 00:35:41.520
- I think we're here.

718
00:35:44.228 --> 00:35:49.228
[thunder rumbles]

719
00:36:02.613 --> 00:36:05.813
[spirit hisses]

720
00:36:05.816 --> 00:36:07.746
- Is that what I think it is?

721
00:36:07.751 --> 00:36:10.951
- We must keep moving.

722
00:36:10.955 --> 00:36:13.285
[spirits roar]

723
00:36:13.290 --> 00:36:14.760
- Oh. man.

724
00:36:14.758 --> 00:36:16.258
I really don't like this.

725
00:36:16.260 --> 00:36:17.830
- Bolin. just stay calm.

726
00:36:17.828 --> 00:36:18.898
There's no reason to--

727
00:36:18.896 --> 00:36:19.926
Panic!

728
00:36:19.930 --> 00:36:21.670
- [veins]

729
00:36:21.665 --> 00:36:23.895
- [grunts]

730
00:36:23.901 --> 00:36:28.901
- Aah!

731
00:36:32.843 --> 00:36:35.513
- Korra. look out!

732
00:36:35.513 --> 00:36:38.643
[grunts]

733
00:36:38.649 --> 00:36:41.189
- Oh. it's in the engine!

734
00:36:41.185 --> 00:36:46.185
[screams]

735
00:36:49.527 --> 00:36:52.527
[mystical music]

736
00:36:56.867 --> 00:36:58.467
[spirit roars]

737
00:36:58.469 --> 00:36:59.769
- [grunts]

738
00:36:59.770 --> 00:37:04.770
[spirit roars]

739
00:37:12.616 --> 00:37:13.586
- Is everyone okay?

740
00:37:13.584 --> 00:37:16.314
- [screams]

741
00:37:16.320 --> 00:37:19.330
I can't stop it.

742
00:37:19.323 --> 00:37:21.393
- I'll save you.
- [screams]

743
00:37:21.392 --> 00:37:22.522
[explosion]

744
00:37:22.526 --> 00:37:24.796
[grunts]

745
00:37:24.795 --> 00:37:29.795
I'm a raft!

746
00:37:40.444 --> 00:37:43.514
Uh. can someone please deflate me?

747
00:37:43.514 --> 00:37:46.914
[air hisses.
Pabu squeaks]

748
00:37:46.917 --> 00:37:48.187
Thank you.

749
00:37:48.185 --> 00:37:49.515
- Oh. great.

750
00:37:49.520 --> 00:37:51.160
There goes our equipment.

751
00:37:51.155 --> 00:37:52.425
Now what are we supposed to do?

752
00:37:52.423 --> 00:37:54.323
- There's only one thing to do.

753
00:37:54.325 --> 00:37:56.555
We have to turn back.
- No.

754
00:37:56.560 --> 00:37:57.930
The solstice is tonight.

755
00:37:57.928 --> 00:37:59.198
We're so close.

756
00:37:59.196 --> 00:38:00.696
- This mission is too dangerous.

757
00:38:00.698 --> 00:38:02.768
We're leaving.
- No. Dad.

758
00:38:02.766 --> 00:38:07.766
You're leaving.

759
00:38:13.237 --> 00:38:15.237
- Don't worry. sir.

760
00:38:15.139 --> 00:38:16.739
I'll keep an eye on Korra for you.

761
00:38:16.840 --> 00:38:21.240
- Thank you. Mako.

762
00:38:21.245 --> 00:38:24.685
[engine revs]

763
00:38:24.682 --> 00:38:27.522
- Let's open this portal
and lead your father

764
00:38:27.518 --> 00:38:29.018
and the entire Southern Water Tribe

765
00:38:29.019 --> 00:38:30.219
in the right direction.

766
00:38:30.220 --> 00:38:32.220
We don't have much time.

767
00:38:32.222 --> 00:38:37.222
- Then what are we waiting for?

768
00:38:47.037 --> 00:38:49.737
So. what exactly were
you and my dad talking about?

769
00:38:49.740 --> 00:38:50.940
- Nothing.

770
00:38:50.941 --> 00:38:52.941
He was just worried
about you. that's all.

771
00:38:52.943 --> 00:38:55.613
- You know. sometimes
I wonder whose side you're on.

772
00:38:55.612 --> 00:38:57.042
- There aren't any sides.

773
00:38:57.047 --> 00:39:00.207
We all just want
to help however we can.

774
00:39:00.217 --> 00:39:05.217
You have to trust
that we're here for you.

775
00:39:05.589 --> 00:39:10.589
- We've arrived.

776
00:39:11.695 --> 00:39:13.865
- Trees frozen in ice.

777
00:39:13.864 --> 00:39:15.834
- It's just like the sacred forest

778
00:39:15.833 --> 00:39:17.703
Tonraq destroyed in the north.

779
00:39:17.701 --> 00:39:20.231
- So what do I do?

780
00:39:20.237 --> 00:39:22.097
- You must find your way
to the heart of the forest

781
00:39:22.106 --> 00:39:24.546
where the dormant spirit portal lies.

782
00:39:24.541 --> 00:39:26.741
From here.
you're on your own.

783
00:39:26.744 --> 00:39:28.044
- Wait a second.

784
00:39:28.045 --> 00:39:29.885
There's no way she's going alone.

785
00:39:29.880 --> 00:39:32.550
- Yeah. if she goes. we go too.

786
00:39:32.549 --> 00:39:34.819
- The Avatar must go alone.

787
00:39:34.818 --> 00:39:36.948
- But I don't have any
connection with the spirits.

788
00:39:36.954 --> 00:39:39.194
In fact.
it seems like they hate me.

789
00:39:39.189 --> 00:39:44.189
- You have to believe in yourself
like I believe in you.

790
00:39:44.628 --> 00:39:45.728
What is it?

791
00:39:45.729 --> 00:39:47.089
- I guess I'm just so used to people

792
00:39:47.097 --> 00:39:49.657
telling me how to do things
that I forgot what it was like

793
00:39:49.666 --> 00:39:51.236
to have someone trust in me.

794
00:39:51.235 --> 00:39:55.575
- Korra. all the past Avatars
live on inside of you.

795
00:39:55.572 --> 00:39:58.142
Let them guide you.

796
00:39:58.142 --> 00:40:03.142
Let them help you
find the light in the dark.

797
00:40:08.952 --> 00:40:10.922
- Wait here.

798
00:40:10.921 --> 00:40:12.921
I'll be okay.

799
00:40:12.923 --> 00:40:17.923
- Good luck.
[Pabu squeaks]

800
00:40:24.768 --> 00:40:29.768
[wind howling]

801
00:40:47.925 --> 00:40:52.925
[ghostly hissing]

802
00:40:57.768 --> 00:41:02.768
- [gasps]
[panting]

803
00:41:03.607 --> 00:41:08.607
[grunts]

804
00:41:08.679 --> 00:41:13.679
[grunts]

805
00:41:25.629 --> 00:41:28.129
The spirit portal.

806
00:41:28.132 --> 00:41:33.132
Amazing.

807
00:41:36.440 --> 00:41:38.640
- [gasps]

808
00:41:38.642 --> 00:41:41.642
[mystical music]

809
00:41:43.180 --> 00:41:48.020
[gasps]

810
00:41:48.018 --> 00:41:53.018
What Avatar is this?

811
00:41:53.857 --> 00:41:58.857
- The light in the dark.

812
00:41:59.696 --> 00:42:04.696
[grunts]

813
00:42:13.944 --> 00:42:18.944
Why isn't it opening?

814
00:42:18.982 --> 00:42:23.982
[gasps]

815
00:42:26.523 --> 00:42:30.023
Come on. portal.
Open!

816
00:42:30.027 --> 00:42:34.927
[spirit hisses]

817
00:42:34.932 --> 00:42:36.262
[grunts]

818
00:42:36.266 --> 00:42:41.266
[gasps]

819
00:42:46.910 --> 00:42:51.910
[grunts]

820
00:43:02.659 --> 00:43:07.659
[warbling chime. rumbling]

821
00:43:08.031 --> 00:43:13.031
Qof!

822
00:43:18.342 --> 00:43:23.342
The spirits dancing in the sky.

823
00:43:26.149 --> 00:43:31.149
- [gasps]

824
00:43:36.126 --> 00:43:38.496
- I can't believe it.

825
00:43:38.495 --> 00:43:43.495
- It's beautiful.

826
00:43:52.609 --> 00:43:57.609
- She did it.

827
00:43:59.149 --> 00:44:01.119
- Hey. Korra. you're back!

828
00:44:01.118 --> 00:44:06.118
Hey. Korra's back.

829
00:44:06.923 --> 00:44:08.293
Wha--huh?

830
00:44:08.292 --> 00:44:11.062
- Why are you initiating
physical contact

831
00:44:11.061 --> 00:44:12.161
with another woman?

832
00:44:12.162 --> 00:44:15.102
- [gulps and laughs nervously]

833
00:44:15.098 --> 00:44:17.898
- Everything you said was true.

834
00:44:17.901 --> 00:44:20.601
- Avatar Korra.
you have taken the first step

835
00:44:20.604 --> 00:44:23.174
in bringing balance back to the South.

836
00:44:23.173 --> 00:44:27.513
and soon. the whole world.

837
00:44:27.511 --> 00:44:31.551
- You never cease to amaze me.
- Thanks.

838
00:44:31.548 --> 00:44:34.678
By the way. I'm really sorry
for being a total pain.

839
00:44:34.685 --> 00:44:36.785
Things were really stressful
and confusing.

840
00:44:36.787 --> 00:44:38.947
It's hard being the Avatar.

841
00:44:38.955 --> 00:44:40.795
- It's harder
being the Avatar's boyfriend.

842
00:44:40.791 --> 00:44:45.791
- [laughs]

843
00:45:08.185 --> 00:45:10.555
What are all your
Northern troops doing here?

844
00:45:10.554 --> 00:45:13.024
- Opening the spirit portal
was only the first step

845
00:45:13.023 --> 00:45:14.563
in getting the Southern Water Tribe

846
00:45:14.558 --> 00:45:16.988
back on its righteous path.

847
00:45:16.993 --> 00:45:18.833
There's more difficult work to be done

848
00:45:18.829 --> 00:45:23.829
before our two tribes are truly united.
